  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Response to Ebola Virus Disease Epidemic in North Kivu and Ituri Provinces</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To improve the collective response to the Ebola epidemic, IOM intends to strengthen and expand its current operations in eastern Democratic Republic of the Congo, in line with the latest Strategic Response Plan (SRP4). The proposed approach focuses on four interventions that will be implemented.  The first will be strengthening the functionality and quality of points of entry (PoE) / points of control (PoC) health screening services, including screening 24/7 a week at strategic PoE / PoC level.  The second will be to improve contact tracing and referral mechanisms at priority PoE / PoC; 3. The third will be strengthening cross-border coordination, participatory mobility mapping and population flow monitoring. Lastly, the project will focus on strengthening disease prevention activities at PoE / PoC through risk communication and community engagement activities. The proposed activities have an immediate impact on the health of the Congolese population and neighboring countries in line to the response to the Ebola Virus Disease outbreak.</narrative>
  </description>
